In the Novomoskovsk area, according to official data, the rocket hit on a farm. As a result, the building was destroyed, equipment was damaged, and one person was injured.

‚ÄúThere was also a missile strike on the territory of Nikopol district. No one was killed. It is still clear how many missiles the enemy has sent to Dnipropetrovsk region, ‚Äùsaid Yevhenia Dudka, a spokeswoman for the Dnipropetrovsk State Emergency Service.

According to her, Pavlograd was also hit. Two missiles damaged the overpass. Communal services are currently restoring the road surface. Traffic is temporarily suspended.

The other day, Russian troops also fired a missile at the Pavlograd-2 railway station, which connects with Donbass. The station was destroyed ‚Äì the railways were damaged, 15 cars derailed, one person died.

Vadym RYZHKOV, The Day, Dnipro

Russian troops have launched several enemy missile strikes in the Dnipropetrovsk region.

This was announced in a Telegram by the head of the Dnipropetrovsk Regional Military Administration Valentyn Reznichenko, as reported by Censor.NET



According to him, in the Novomoskovsk area, the rocket hit the territory of a farm. Damaged equipment. One person was injured.

"A viaduct was targeted in Pavlohrad. Traffic was suspended on the road. A missile strike also hit the territory of the Nikopol district. No one was killed," he said.

Read more: Enemy aircraft took off from Crimea to Mykolaiv

Russia-Ukraine war updates, photo/video. Russian invasion of Ukraine began on February 24. Many Ukrainian cities have been destroyed by rocket attacks, captured or remain under siege. Negotiations: Ukraine is ready to accept a neutral status with guarantees from the West, Moscow announced a reduction in attacks around Kyiv and Chernigov and a focus on the Donbass. Unprecedentedly severe sanctions against Russia are destroying Russian economy. According to UN estimates, more than five million refugees were forced to leave their homes.
